[Human infection with the rickettsial cause of Q fever is a zoonosis
usually spread by aerosol from an infected animal. Like the outbreak in
Chamonix, France earlier this year cited below, the zoonotic reservoir may
not be identified. It can be postulated that an infected animal such as a
cat contaminated the environment and an aerosol resulted. The diagnostic
criteria to make the diagnosis of Q fever is not given here. Hopefully, a
formal public health epidemiologic investigation will assist in finding a
source. -Mod.LL]
